The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, June 15, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, June 14: Car sales recorded a 9.88 per cent growth in May compared with 32.4 per cent in April. Maruti and the Tatas offset the negative growth posted by Hyundai in May. Total car sales, however, increased to 60,618 in May from over 55,165 units in the year-ago period. According to data released by the Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers today, the performance in other auto segments, including two wheelers and commercial vehicles, continued to be good in the current financial year.																								 New Delhi, June 14: The Indian economy will grow in excess of 6 per cent in 2004-05, the World Bank today said. It has a potential of much higher growth if right policies are followed, country director Michael F. Carter said.																								 New Delhi, June 14: The Telecom Regulatory Authority of India (Trai) will submit its report on FM radio licensing to the government by the middle of next week, sources said today. 																								 Mumbai, June 14: Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation (HSBC) in India has reported a 32 per cent rise in net profit (after extraordinary expenses) at Rs 197.8 crore in 2003-04 compared with Rs 150.3 crore in 2002-03.																								 New Delhi, June 14: The Singapore-based Flextronics International has priced its open offer for 20 per cent of the paid-up equity capital of Hughes Software Systems at Rs 548 a share.
